The database consists of four tables:
orders: Contains details about customer orders.
order_details: Stores information on pizzas included in each order.
pizzas: Lists available pizzas along with their prices and sizes.
pizza_types: Defines different pizza types and their categories.

The project is structured into three levels: Basic, Intermediate, and Advanced, with progressively complex SQL queries to explore sales trends and performance metrics.

Objectives

Basic Queries
Retrieve the total number of orders placed.
Calculate the total revenue generated from pizza sales.
Identify the highest-priced pizza.
Determine the most common pizza size ordered.
List the top 5 most ordered pizza types along with their quantities.

Intermediate Queries
Find the total quantity of each pizza category ordered by joining relevant tables.
Analyze the distribution of orders by hour of the day.
Determine the category-wise distribution of pizzas.
Group the orders by date and calculate the average number of pizzas ordered per day.
Identify the top 3 most ordered pizza types based on revenue.

Advanced Queries
Calculate the percentage contribution of each pizza type to total revenue.
Analyze cumulative revenue generation over time.
Determine the top 3 most ordered pizza types based on revenue for each pizza category.
